## BACKLOG-083 - Show green or red auth status with re-auth actions
- Status: Grooming
- Owner: Paula Product
- Requester: current session
- Date added: 2026-04-15
- Updated: 2026-04-15T12:07:21.000Z
- Due Date: 
- Priority: P1
- Effort: 3
- Sprint Assigned: 
- Ready for Implementation?: No
- Tech handoff owner: Unassigned
- Summary: Show a realistic green or red status indicator for each project integration and give users a simple setup or re-auth action.
- Outcome / user value: Users can tell at a glance whether the current project credentials are usable and can recover expired or invalid auth without digging through hidden config.
- Scope notes: In scope, a realistic-looking green status LED when a project's current integration setup validates, a red LED when credentials are missing, invalid, or expired, and one simple affordance on the row to set up or re-auth that integration. In scope, updating the row state after setup or re-auth without making the whole config panel feel blocked. Out of scope, adding extra traffic-light states, forcing users into log inspection, or changing the supported integration catalog.
- Acceptance criteria:
  - [ ] Each supported project integration row can show a green status indicator when the current stored credentials or auth setup validate successfully.
  - [ ] Each supported project integration row shows a red status indicator when the current stored credentials are invalid, missing, or expired.
  - [ ] Each row exposes a visible setup or re-auth action so the user can repair an invalid integration from the same config surface.
  - [ ] After a successful setup or re-auth, the row can update from red to green without requiring the user to rebuild the whole project context manually.
  - [ ] A validation problem on one integration row does not prevent the rest of the config panel from remaining usable.
- Dependencies: BACKLOG-081, per-integration validation hooks, auth and re-auth flows, config-row status rendering.
