  - [ ] When an integration is shared, the invited user can access that integration only inside the shared project context rather than as a new global credential.
  - [ ] When an integration is not shared, the invited user sees a clear project-level unavailable or unconfigured state instead of silently inheriting access.
  - [ ] The story defines how credential rotation or revocation propagates to users who received the shared project integration.
