- Due Date: 
- Priority: P1
- Effort: 2
- Sprint Assigned: 
- Ready for Implementation?: No
- Tech handoff owner: Unassigned
- Summary: Define Paula startup behavior so users can choose a reasoning level in system settings independently of the selected model.
- Outcome / user value: Teams can tune speed versus depth intentionally from one visible settings path without being forced into a codex-model-specific choice.
- Scope notes: In scope, defining one system-settings control for Paula startup reasoning level, applying that stored setting to future Paula launches regardless of which supported model is chosen, and clarifying how the UI handles models that support different reasoning levels. In scope, defining validation and fallback behavior when the stored reasoning level is unavailable for the chosen model, plus whether the setting affects only new Paula sessions or also already running ones. Out of scope, forcing a specific default model, per-message reasoning changes inside an active chat, separate per-project model policies, or changing non-Paula agents.
- Acceptance criteria:
  - [ ] The story defines one user-visible system-settings control for Paula reasoning level.
  - [ ] The reasoning setting is not tied to a single codex-specific model choice and can be used with any supported Paula model.
  - [ ] New Paula launches apply the stored reasoning level when the chosen model supports it.
  - [ ] If the chosen model does not support the stored reasoning level, the product shows a clear validation or fallback path before launch instead of silently ignoring the mismatch.
  - [ ] The story defines whether changing the reasoning setting affects only new Paula sessions and how that is surfaced to the user.
  - [ ] The first release stays scoped to startup behavior and does not add live per-message reasoning changes.
- Dependencies: Paula agent launch flow, system settings storage, model capability mapping, startup configuration read path.
