- Summary: Support date-based sprint planning with fixed 7-day and 14-day cadences anchored from one board-level sprint start date.
- Outcome / user value: Users can trust that dated sprint windows follow a predictable cadence instead of ambiguous or ad hoc time boxes.
- Scope notes: In scope, supporting only `7-day` and `14-day` cadences for the first release, storing one board-level anchor start date, deriving each sprint window as contiguous non-overlapping calendar ranges from that anchor, and treating the end date as inclusive. In scope, identifying the current sprint by the local calendar date falling within a derived window. In scope, applying cadence changes only from an explicit effective date forward so historical sprint windows keep their original boundaries. Out of scope, planning navigation layout, ticket-assignment UI, or changing story-level backlog fields on this card.
- Acceptance criteria:
  - [ ] The product supports exactly two date-based sprint cadences for v1: `7-day` and `14-day`.
  - [ ] A board stores one anchor sprint start date, and each subsequent sprint window is derived from that anchor as a contiguous non-overlapping range.
  - [ ] Each sprint end date is computed as the inclusive final day of the selected cadence window.
  - [ ] The current sprint is the derived window that contains the user's local current date.
  - [ ] When a team changes cadence, the change takes effect only from a user-chosen future effective date, and previously derived sprint windows remain unchanged.
- Dependencies: date-based planning configuration, local-date handling, sprint-window derivation.
