- Summary: Host both the board UI and its markdown backlog file online behind authenticated workspace access so the markdown file remains the durable source of truth.
- Outcome / user value: Users can open and edit the backlog from anywhere through a stable online interface instead of depending on a local-only setup.
- Scope notes: In scope, a hosted v1 that includes both the board UI and one hosted markdown backlog file per workspace, authenticated access for workspace members, latest-version read-before-write protection, and backup coverage for hosted edits. In scope, rejecting writes on version mismatch rather than silently merging conflicting changes. Out of scope, choosing a specific cloud vendor, supporting anonymous access, or changing the markdown schema.
- Acceptance criteria:
  - [ ] Hosted v1 includes both the online board UI and a hosted markdown backlog file that remains the source of truth for backlog content.
  - [ ] Opening or editing the hosted board requires authenticated workspace access.
  - [ ] Every hosted write reads the latest file version first and rejects the write with a visible retry path when the file changed in the meantime.
  - [ ] Hosted editing keeps pre-write backup coverage so users are not one failed write away from losing backlog history.
  - [ ] The product does not require a separate hidden database copy of story content to function in the hosted mode.
- Dependencies: write-safety model, hosted authentication decision, hosted storage decision.
