- Summary: Add support for a `Blocked` story status, legacy-format migration handling, and an urgent blocked-card treatment that keeps blocked work in its current lane.
- Outcome / user value: Teams can spot stalled work immediately without losing workflow context, while older backlog files remain usable after blocked-state support is introduced.
- Scope notes: In scope, adding `Blocked` as a supported status in the markdown workflow, updating templates and legacy loading behavior to recognize the expanded status set, rendering blocked cards with both a red background and a red border, and keeping blocked stories in their current lane rather than moving them to a dedicated swimlane. In scope, keeping blocked stories counted as active work in normal lane totals while also exposing a separate blocked counter in the top bar. Out of scope, adding a new top-level blocked lane, silently rewriting older backlog files, or hiding blocked stories from their current workflow context.
- Acceptance criteria:
  - [ ] A blocked ticket remains visible in its existing workflow lane instead of moving into a separate blocked lane.
  - [ ] Blocked tickets use a clearly urgent visual treatment that is stronger than the normal card styling.
  - [ ] The board still shows blocked work in normal lane totals so stalled work does not disappear from active workflow counts.
  - [ ] The top bar exposes blocked work as a separate summary count.
  - [ ] Older backlog inputs that predate blocked-state support still load without forcing manual backlog cleanup.
